You're going to need to use variables as your first step to set me free!
Variables are like containters that can hold certain kinds of data, usually either numbers, text, decimal numbers and true/false values. Unless specified beforehand, variables can be changed to hold what you want when you want, as long as they're holding the type of data they're designed to hold, for example an integer variable could only hold an integer, and not a string.
In C#.... variables that holds text are called Strings, ones that hold whole numbers are called integers, written as or int for easy typing decimal numbers are called doubles and values that have either a true or false value are called booleans, written as bool for easy typing
